									  Richard E. Borowy					  
Richard E. Borowy


Director of Alternative Investments
Richard E. Borowy is Director of Alternative Investments. Rich has over 26 years of industry experience. As the Director of Alternative Investments at Pitcairn, he is responsible for overseeing all alternative managers on the investment platform including manager selection, due diligence, and monitoring. In addition, Rich manages the Pitcairn Alternative Investment Fund and Pitcairn Private Equity Fund and conducts alternative investment product research and portfolio management for these funds. As a member of the Investment Strategy committee and the Due Diligence committee, Rich plays an important role in Pitcairn’s investment decision-making process. Before assuming his current role, Rich was a Senior Equity Analyst at Pitcairn, responsible for researching and analyzing private investment opportunities.  
Prior to joining Pitcairn in 1987, Rich worked as a securities analyst at Cheng Management where he developed models to analyze the performance of high growth companies in stock portfolios. He earned his MBA at Columbia University, his MS in Chemistry at the University of Connecticut and his BA at Western Connecticut State College.
 
 
 
 

